translated: Brinkenberg, Gustaf Victor Hugo, assistant minister, Lerdala, born on June 10th, 1897 in Vassända-Naglum, Älvsborg county. Married once in 1921 to Sigrid Andersson, with whom he had five children: Bengt born in 1922, Lars born in 1925, Gunnar born in 1933, Ulla born in 1935, and Lena born in 1942. Brinkenberg passed his high school exam in Vänersborg in 1918, his Bachelor of Divinity in 1927, and his practical theology exam in 1931. He was ordained in the diocese of Skara in 1932 and worked as an assistant minister in Rångedala from 1932 to 1934, interim assistant minister there in 1934, minister in Berg from 1935, and a military pastor from 1939. He served as a staff member of the Water Authority from 1920 to 1924 and as a private teacher from 1924 to 1930. He was the vice-chairman of the school board, a member of the municipal council, and a member of the child welfare committee. He wrote poetry, mystery plays, and treatises on church doctrine. He enjoyed studying history and ecology.
